.TH LOA-OBSIDIAN-SYNC 1 "2026-03-23" "Library Of Alexandria" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
obsidian sync \- Sync managed Alexandria notes into an Obsidian vault
.SH SYNOPSIS
alexandria> obsidian sync
.br
alexandria> obsidian sync /path/to/your/vault
.SH DESCRIPTION
Syncs managed markdown notes in:
.br
\fB<vault>/Alexandria/\fR
.br
Notes include unified rich frontmatter, Bases GUI files, Dataview dashboards,
MOC pages, smart analysis pages, template files, and a sync report.
.br
Sync consolidates legacy duplicate Alexandria export roots in the vault
when they are detected as Alexandria-managed folders.
.br
Tags that match genre names are filtered from Obsidian tag output to avoid overlap.
.br
Only the Alexandria managed block inside each note is replaced, preserving
manual text in Connections/Analysis/Notes sections while re-enforcing
the standard note template structure.
.br
If no path is provided, the previously configured vault path is used.
.br
If no vault has been configured yet, you can first run:
.br
\fBexport obsidian <vault_path>\fR
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
alexandria> obsidian sync
.TP
alexandria> obsidian sync ~/Documents/MyVault
.SH SEE ALSO
loa(1), loa-export-obsidian(1), loa-obsidian-doctor(1), loa-obsidian-open(1)
.SH AUTHOR
